## Limitations

The report is limited by the availability of sources primarily in English, which may not fully capture the experiences of all affected communities. Additionally, the retrospective nature of many studies on apartheid means that some personal accounts and data may be subject to recall bias. The ongoing socio-political changes in South Africa also mean that the legacy of apartheid is continuously evolving, which may not be fully reflected in historical analyses.

